Fondly referred to as the "Tanglewood" of the West Coast, the Oregon Coast Music Festival will celebrate the 31st and final year for Maestro James Paul and welcome guest conductor, Martin Majkut for its 46th Season. This annual festival boasts two full weeks, including three Saturdays, of classical music and music education for all ages.

July 13th - 27th, 2024

Step into the world of mixology with our Cocktail Series, guided by Ryan, our expert bartender at 7 Devils Waterfront Alehouse. Across three classes you'll delve into the art of mixology and master the basics.

Treat yourself or a loved one to the gift of mixology mastery! Call us at (541) 808-2699 or visit us to purchase tickets. Choose any combination you prefer: take all three, or opt for just one or two!

December 21st - Craft & Batch: Kick off the series by learning the ropes of creating (and drinking) two signature cocktails and mastering the skill of batching one of them (which you can take home with you to share over the holidays). $75/person & approximately 1.5 to 2 hours long. Begins at 6:30 PM

description:
THE BRIGHTEST AND MOST BEAUTIFUL PLACE ON THE OREGON COAST SHINES

Holiday Lights are set to sparkle again on Oregon’s Adventure Coast this season at Shore Acres State Park. Perched on rugged cliffs overlooking the Pacific Ocean, Shore Acres State Park is famous for its beautiful 7-acre botanical gardens and Japanese lily pond. Visitors get a chance to stroll through this holiday tradition every night from 4:30pm to 9:00pm, Thanksgiving through New Year’s Eve – including Christmas Eve and Christmas Day. It has become a real holiday tradition for the whole family. 

Admission is always free! However, parking at Shore Acres any time of the year is $5.

New Year's Eve Neon Masquerade Ball at Front Street Provisioners

Come as you are or dress to impress and nab a pic of your whole squad at the complimentary photo booth by Curtis Candids. Bring your GLOW, we've got plenty of black lights to dance under! No mask? No problem! Stop by our DIY mask-making table or enjoy our professional face painting booth by the very talented Lauren Reichlein! Lauren will be accepting cash payments only for face painting services. Get creative, prizes for crew favorites! Masks must be removed for ID checks and face paint must be ID - identifiable for the Bar per OLCC.
